{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/2018-08-21-quick-and-not-so-dirty-cors-proxy/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"ohmybuck"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"cdd013d9-1747-548e-9e9f-c6ce189089c0","excerpt":"Late one night I got a slack message from one of my colleagues:  It’s a pretty common issue - you’re trying to integrate with another company or 3rd party API…","html":"<p>Late one night I got a slack message from one of my colleagues:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/b7a4b7b227e18ff61e9338ff1f5f81bb/f793b/2018-08-21-quick-and-not-so-dirty-cors-proxy.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 28.37837837837838%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Message: I need help with a proxy\"\n        title=\"Message: I need help with a proxy\"\n        src=\"/static/b7a4b7b227e18ff61e9338ff1f5f81bb/fcda8/2018-08-21-quick-and-not-so-dirty-cors-proxy.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/b7a4b7b227e18ff61e9338ff1f5f81bb/12f09/2018-08-21-quick-and-not-so-dirty-cors-proxy.png 148w,\n/static/b7a4b7b227e18ff61e9338ff1f5f81bb/e4a3f/2018-08-21-quick-and-not-so-dirty-cors-proxy.png 295w,\n/static/b7a4b7b227e18ff61e9338ff1f5f81bb/fcda8/2018-08-21-quick-and-not-so-dirty-cors-proxy.png 590w,\n/static/b7a4b7b227e18ff61e9338ff1f5f81bb/efc66/2018-08-21-quick-and-not-so-dirty-cors-proxy.png 885w,\n/static/b7a4b7b227e18ff61e9338ff1f5f81bb/c83ae/2018-08-21-quick-and-not-so-dirty-cors-proxy.png 1180w,\n/static/b7a4b7b227e18ff61e9338ff1f5f81bb/f793b/2018-08-21-quick-and-not-so-dirty-cors-proxy.png 1404w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>It’s a pretty common issue - you’re trying to integrate with another company or 3rd party API and:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>You have a an API key you can’t distribute to users as it may be a paid service (Think <a href=\"https://www.loqate.com/\">Loquate/ex-Postcode Anywhere</a>)</li>\n<li>The other service hasn’t whitelisted your domain to make calls to it (<a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/CORS\">CORS</a>)</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>The main issue</h2>\n<p>Sometimes people are bogged down with other work, sysOps is nervous, or even worse slow. This could be due to company process and governance - so not necessarily their fault, but it’s still a blocker. If we don’t have access to a backend, one option is to spin up our own proxy server.</p>\n<p>I’m not the biggest fan of <a href=\"https://www.heroku.com/\">Heroku</a> for use as a production server, however in this case, I can’t think of a better tool for the job.</p>\n<h2>The code</h2>\n<p>Luckily for us, <a href=\"https://www.walkscore.com/\">Walkscore</a> provided a sample script for <a href=\"https://www.walkscore.com/professional/api-sample-code.php\">Making a Server-Side API Request</a>.</p>\n<p>I’ve adapted it below to use environmental variables for the API key, and if you look at the <a href=\"https://gitlab.com/olmesm/walkscore-heroku-service\">Dirty Proxy Repo</a> you’ll see how I deploy it to <a href=\"https://www.heroku.com/\">Heroku</a></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"php\"><pre class=\"language-php\"><code class=\"language-php\"><span class=\"token php language-php\"><span class=\"token delimiter important\">&lt;?</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Sort out our CORS Issues</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">header</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string double-quoted-string\">\"Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">header</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string double-quoted-string\">\"Access-Control-Allow-Headers: X-Requested-With\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Function to make a request to the Walkscore API</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">getWalkScore</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token variable\">$lat</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token variable\">$lon</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token variable\">$address</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token comment\">// Get API Key set in the environment varibles</span>\n  <span class=\"token variable\">$WALKSCORE_API_KEY</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">getenv</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string single-quoted-string\">'WALKSCORE_API_KEY'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n  <span class=\"token variable\">$address</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token function\">urlencode</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token variable\">$address</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token variable\">$url</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string double-quoted-string\">\"http://api.walkscore.com/score?format=json&amp;address=<span class=\"token interpolation\"><span class=\"token variable\">$address</span></span>\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token variable\">$url</span> <span class=\"token operator\">.=</span> <span class=\"token string double-quoted-string\">\"&amp;lat=<span class=\"token interpolation\"><span class=\"token variable\">$lat</span></span>&amp;lon=<span class=\"token interpolation\"><span class=\"token variable\">$lon</span></span>&amp;wsapikey=<span class=\"token interpolation\"><span class=\"token variable\">$WALKSCORE_API_KEY</span></span>\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token variable\">$str</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> @<span class=\"token function\">file_get_contents</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token variable\">$url</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token variable\">$str</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Get the URL parameters \"lat\", \"lon\", and \"adress\"</span>\n<span class=\"token variable\">$lat</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token variable\">$_GET</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string single-quoted-string\">'lat'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token variable\">$lon</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token variable\">$_GET</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string single-quoted-string\">'lon'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token variable\">$address</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">stripslashes</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token variable\">$_GET</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string single-quoted-string\">'address'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token variable\">$json</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">getWalkScore</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token variable\">$lat</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span><span class=\"token variable\">$lon</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span><span class=\"token variable\">$address</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">echo</span> <span class=\"token variable\">$json</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token delimiter important\">?></span></span></code></pre></div>\n<p><a href=\"https://gitlab.com/olmesm/walkscore-heroku-service\">Dirty Proxy Repo</a></p>\n<!-- References -->","frontmatter":{"title":"Quick and not-so-dirty CORS proxy","date":"August 21, 2018","description":"Get a proxy up and running for an external service"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/2018-08-21-quick-and-not-so-dirty-cors-proxy/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/2018-08-12-build-a-react-website-with-full-cicd-in-two-minutes/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Build a React Website with full CI/CD in less than 2 minutes","draft":null}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/2018-08-25-setup-a-pi-for-node-development/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Setup a pi for node development","draft":null}}}}}